/*Problem- Reverse Linked List II
Difficulty- Medium
Platform- Leetcode
Frequency-0ms
Approach- LinkedList, Two Pointer

Create a dummy node pointing to head to handle edge cases.
Move a pointer (prev) to the node just before the left position.
Start reversing nodes between left and right using head insertion method.
In every iteration take next node and place it after prev.
This reverses the sublist in one traversal without extra space.
Return dummy.next as the new head.

Solution-*/
class Solution {
    public ListNode reverseBetween(ListNode head, int left, int right) {

        if(head == null || left == right)
            return head;

        ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0);
        dummy.next = head;

        ListNode prev = dummy;

        for(int i = 1; i < left; i++){
            prev = prev.next;
        }

        ListNode curr = prev.next;

        for(int i = 0; i < right - left; i++){
            ListNode temp = curr.next;
            curr.next = temp.next;
            temp.next = prev.next;
            prev.next = temp;
        }

        return dummy.next;
    }
}
